<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Trunk slender and cylindrical, TrL 59-67% of TL. Rump conical, with both pseudosegments somewhat swollen and strong arched up dorsally and roofing the foot, the posterior rim of the second pseudosegment creased, RL 8-10% of TL.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Foot short with three pseudosegments, FL 6-8% of TL. Bulbous spurs short and triangular shape, with distinct tips and wide interspace, base swollen. The width of interspace 114% of SL, 97% of the swollen width. Three stout unsegmented toes of the same length. Trophi small, dental formula 3/3.</paragraph>
